def _get_grouper(
    obj,
    key=None,
    axis=0,
    level=None,
    sort=True,
    observed=False,
    mutated=False,
    validate=True,
):
    if axis == 1:
        if is_list_like(key):
            keys = key
        else:
            keys = [key]

        group_axis = obj._get_axis(1)

        groupings = []
        exclusions = []

        for key in keys:
            if key in obj.columns:
                col_values = obj[key]
                ping = Grouping(group_axis, col_values, obj=obj, name=key, level=level, sort=sort, observed=observed, in_axis=True)
                groupings.append(ping)
                exclusions.append(key)
            else:
                raise KeyError(key)

        grouper = BaseGrouper(group_axis, groupings, sort=sort, mutated=mutated)
        return grouper, exclusions, obj
